===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|𡿧|火|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t1=flood calamity|t2=fire|tr=*tsˤə;tsˤəh}}.

From {{zh-l|𡿧}}, an oracle-bone graph of three zigzag strokes depicting flowing water; forms with a horizontal stroke phoneticize the middle stroke as {{och-l|才|tr=*dzˤə}}. <ref>陳劍「說「昔」字並論「𡿧」形的真正來源」『饒宗頤國學院院刊』第八期 香港浸會大學饒宗頤國學院、2021年、1–46頁。</ref>

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tsə||to be hot}}; cognate with {{cog|my|ဆာ|t=hungry, thirsty}}, {{cog|bo|ཚ|t=hot, intense}}, and {{och-l|菑|field cleared by slash and burn}} (STEDT), which is its r-causative ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

