===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|わざわい|yomi=k|alt=災い,禍,殃}}
{{IPAchar|/wazapapi/}} → {{IPAchar|/wazaɸaɸi/}} → {{IPAchar|/wazawahi/}} → {{IPAchar|/wazawai/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=わざわい}}. Originally a compound of {{ja-r|業|わざ|deed, doings}}, in reference to the doings of the {{ja-r|神|かみ|gods, spirits}} + {{ja-r|linkto=這う|這い|はい|lit=crawling|spreading widely}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref> Compare the etymology of {{ja-r|linkto=幸#sakiwai|幸|さきわい|good fortune}}. Compare also the connotations of the English term {{m|en|act of God}} in reference to disasters.

Often spelled {{ja-r|災い|わざわい}} with the trailing [[okurigana]] {{ja-r|い}} to make the reading more explicit.

